               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) ʾO-ʾǝgziʾǝyä ʾIyasus Krǝstos ʿǝqäbänni ... “Oh My Lord Jesus Christ,
                     protect me ...” (litanical prayer to Christ) (fols. 4r-19r) (s. S.GRÉBAUT, “La
                     prière ‘ʿƎqäbänni’ ou les litanies du Christ”, Orientalia nuova ser. 4, 1935,
                     426-40)
 II) ʾAstäbqʷǝʿot ʾǝntä za-Sǝmʿon ʿamdawi “Prayers of Simeon
                     Stylite” (fols. 19r-74v) (s. P.LEANDER, "ʾAstabqueʿōt ʾǝnta za-Semʿōn ʿamdāwī,
                     nach Handschriften in Uppsala und Berlin herausgegeben", Le Monde Oriental 11,
                     1917, 81-130)
 III) Malkǝʾ-hymn to St Mary (fols. 74v-81v, 1r-3r) (ascribed
                     to ʾabbā Giyorgis of Gāsǝč̣č̣ā) (s. ChRep 196, no. 91).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I contains the embedded colophon (<locus target="#18v">18v</locus>)
                        which states that the book was translated from a Western/Occidental language
                        and that Gabra Krǝstos was the translator:</note>
                     <note>… ተርጎምክዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አነ፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ እምነገረ፡ አፍርንጊ፡ ኀበ፡ ነገረ፡ ኢትዮጵያ፡</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text III is ascribed to ʾabbā Giyorgis of Gāsǝč̣č̣ā. The traditional
                        title is Ṣalot za-ʾabba Giyorgis “Prayer of ʾabbā Giyorgis”. The text is
                        included in Maṣḥafa gǝbra ḥǝmāmāt “Book of the Rite of the Holy Week” (s.
                        Ethiopian Orthodox Church (ed.), Gǝbra ḥǝmāmāt, Addis Abäba 1942 A.M.
                        [1949/50 A.D.], repr. 1972 A.M. [1979/50],<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES471477">471-477</ref>). The beginning section of the prayer, ዘሌሊት (za-lelit,
                        “for the night hours”), is missing. Here, the text has been interrupted on
                        the last fol. because of the lack of space, the rest having been added on
                        the fly-leaves.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
